"Terraise" turned a 1-star or 2-star experience into a 5-star experience.  We called in an order for pick-up and unbeknownst to us, the guy who took the order got it wrong.  Well... we didn't figure it out until we were back at our offices.  When I opened my sandwich, the paper wrapping was held together with a sticker that said "We Deliver."  So I called and spoke to "Ray."  He didn't identify himself, and he continuously interrupted me and was obviously distracted.  Horrible.  I asked to speak to his manager "Terraise."  I told her the problem and asked her if she'd be so kind to DELIVER the proper sandwich.  Not only did she agree to deliver a replacement sandwich, she also offered some free chips and soda!  No thanks - but THANKS A MILLION for delivering a replacement sandwich.  Terraise - you are awesome!  (Ray needs a little training...)

Great food,  fast service! For the people complaining about long delivery times, think about what time it was when you ordered. If it was between 11:30 and 2 that's because they get over 100 orders in those 2 hours alone. Those delivery drivers take 3 to 4 orders at a time when they leave for a delivery, so yeah, it's gonna take some time. I recommend ordering your food earlier in the day (ex. 11:00) and put a delay on it to the time you want to receive it (ex. 1:00). I've never gotten my food late when I did it that way and I've even gotten it early!

I stopped in here at this store today for a quick lunch since I was on the road; this was my 1st time at a Jimmy Johns.  I was curious to try it out after listening to the commercials.  First, I must say the sandwich was delicious... and it was seriously done, wrapped and ready to go before I even finished paying; it really was as fast as they claim in the commercials.  It was not all messy or thrown together so it was not difficult to eat and stay clean.  Now I wish I had ordered 2 sandwiches!  But I also have to say that the staff was very friendly and welcoming.  I mentioned to the man that greeted me as I walked in (I did not catch his name) that I had never been there before; he took time to walk through how everything worked, what sandwiches were their best sellers and how to order.  I always like to acknowledge top notch customer service when I can and this guy went above and beyond; he had a great demeanor.  So many places these days are staffed by people that you can tell don't want to be there and it shows; this was the exact opposite and I felt like they appreciated my business.  I will definitely be back to Jimmy Johns and I will recommend this store to everyone.
